<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="40.[836,1529,1511,1760]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[932,1210,1512,1540]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Diagnostic Features:</emphasis>
This species resembles the abdominal markings of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tanikawa, 1998" authorityName="Tanikawa" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Spheropistha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyashitai">
<emphasis box="[1212,1529,1548,1577]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Spheropistha miyashitai</emphasis>
(Tanikawa, 
<number box="[990,1059,1585,1614]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It can be separated from the latter in terms of (
<number box="[1001,1014,1621,1650]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="1.0">1</number>
) body size, (
<number box="[1188,1205,1621,1650]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="2.0">2</number>
) color pattern, (
<number box="[1418,1434,1621,1650]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="3.0">3</number>
) shape of the carapace both dorsally and laterally, (
<number box="[845,863,1695,1724]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="4.0">4</number>
) position of the spinnerets, and (
<number box="[1369,1385,1695,1724]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" value="5.0">5</number>
) epigynal structure.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
